Program: Outlook
Title: Football Saved me from Rwanda Genocide
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0275yvp
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 1 Oct 2014
Eric Murangwa is a Rwandan goalkeeper who was protected by his fans during the genocide twenty years ago - he says football saved his life and he's now using the sport to promote peace and reconciliation in his homeland. Ron Finley is a guerilla gardener from Los Angeles - he tells Lucy Ash about his battle to plant vegetables in front of his house. Albert Mazibuko is one of the longest serving members of Ladysmith Black Mambazo - the South African singing group created over 50 years ago. (Photo: Eric Murangwa courstesy of Eric Murangwa) Show less